JLtools 0.9
		    JLtools Extensible Compiler Toolkit

When reading this file you have already downloaded and unpacked the JLtools Distribution. Your installation directory contains the following sub-folders:

  - src: the complete source code of JLtools 0.9
  - lib: the JLtools library files and the "CUP Parser Generator for Java" library (a Copyright notice for CUP can be found at the end of this document) 
  - doc: the documentations about writing JLtools extensions 
  - demo: Jif sample programs
  - images: Logos

Installation Instructions
--------------------------

First ensure javac is in your path and that you are using JDK 1.2
or later.  

On Unix, do:

	sh ./configure
	PATH=$PATH:<your-install-directory>/bin

On NT, you will need the Cygwin environment. While running sh, do:

	sh ./configure
	set PATH=%PATH%;<your-install-directory>\bin


For more information:
---------------------

For information on how to run the JLtools translator (jlc) from the command line, see the file README-JLC.txt

For information on specific Java language extensions included with
this release (e.g. Jif, PolyJ, etc.), see the appropriate README-*
file in this directory.

For information on rebuilding JLtools, see the file src/README.


